;;; Tables and accessors mapping SubL symbols to their C-backend names.
;;; Only the four initialize-* functions retain Java bodies; all 12 other
;;; declareFunction entries were stripped by LarKC and are represented as
;;; one-line comment stubs at their source-order positions.
;;;
;;; Data-symbol package note: the Java tables contain symbols from both the
;;; default package and the SUBLISP package.  Clyc has no SUBLISP package,
;;; so those symbols are interned into :clyc alongside their default-package
;;; counterparts.  This creates three known EQ collisions (FILE-LENGTH,
;;; GET-FILE-POSITION, STREAM-LINE-COLUMN) where both a SUBLISP-qualified
;;; and an unqualified symbol of the same name appear in
;;; *c-backend-defined-function-name-data*.  TODO: once a SUBLISP package
;;; is defined project-wide, restore the package-qualified symbol identities.

